then was a lot of money.

01:48:15.260 --> 01:48:18.090
And so, I began to
photograph everything.

01:48:18.090 --> 01:48:22.300
The. That's one of my pictures.

01:48:22.300 --> 01:48:26.930
The one in the truck
is one of my pictures.

01:48:26.930 --> 01:48:31.280
I photographed the station
from the beginning when we went

01:48:31.280 --> 01:48:35.100
to visit KBBF in
Santa Rosa California,

01:48:35.100 --> 01:48:39.690
which was the first bilingual
station in the country.

01:48:39.690 --> 01:48:44.070
And we were, none of us
had experience in radio.

01:48:44.070 --> 01:48:48.760
And so, we learned that there
was a station in Santa Rosa.

01:48:48.760 --> 01:48:51.440
And so, we took a group of
us there to talk to them.

01:48:51.440 --> 01:48:56.140
And so, I have photographs
from those earlier periods.

01:48:56.140 --> 01:48:59.750
Also, because we were poor,
we did all of our construction

01:48:59.750 --> 01:49:02.100
on our radio station by hand.

01:49:02.100 --> 01:49:03.960
We did the tower.

01:49:03.960 --> 01:49:07.260
We were not engineers, but
with the help of one engineer,

01:49:07.260 --> 01:49:09.020
we got volunteers,
community volunteers.

01:49:09.020 --> 01:49:11.790
So, it was really a station
that was built by the community.

01:49:11.790 --> 01:49:14.620
So, we did the tower.

01:49:14.620 --> 01:49:16.520
We put up the antenna.

01:49:16.520 --> 01:49:18.580
We dug the holes
on the mountain.

01:49:18.580 --> 01:49:23.230
Our tower is located on
Yakima National Tribal Land.

01:49:23.230 --> 01:49:26.280
We worked with them on
getting a reasonable price.

01:49:26.280 --> 01:49:28.730
And so, we did all
of the digging

01:49:28.730 --> 01:49:30.030
and the moving of the rocks.

01:49:30.030 --> 01:49:31.940
Everything was done by
hand for Radio KDNA.

01:49:31.940 --> 01:49:35.600
It's a very special
radio station,

01:49:35.600 --> 01:49:38.190
in that its way up
in the Northwest.

01:49:38.190 --> 01:49:41.810
Many people didn't even know
there were Spanish people living

01:49:41.810 --> 01:49:43.900
in the Northwest at the time.

01:49:43.900 --> 01:49:46.910
And when the station first
went in the air, on the air,

01:49:46.910 --> 01:49:51.580
our audience was
really not immigrants,

01:49:51.580 --> 01:49:55.920
because the first arrivals to
do agriculture work in the State

01:49:55.920 --> 01:50:01.320
of Washington were
American citizens, Texans,

01:50:01.320 --> 01:50:04.930
people from California, people
from the Midwest that moved

01:50:04.930 --> 01:50:09.370
into Washington State, but
primarily [foreign language].

01:50:09.370 --> 01:50:14.580
And then, later on, as, of
course, immigration increases,

01:50:14.580 --> 01:50:16.900
the station, of course, which
is one of the beautiful things

01:50:16.900 --> 01:50:20.560
about radio is its flexibility
to be able to really focus

01:50:20.560 --> 01:50:22.030
on the needs of its community.

01:50:22.030 --> 01:50:25.560
It was able to then adjust
itself to meet the needs of,

01:50:25.560 --> 01:50:28.090
you know, the immigrants that
were moving into the valley.

01:50:28.090 --> 01:50:30.430
So, its programming has
changed over the years,

01:50:30.430 --> 01:50:33.970
but initially it was
U.S. citizen Spanish

01:50:33.970 --> 01:50:35.830
speaking audience.

01:50:35.830 --> 01:50:38.360
So, that's just a little
bit of the history.

01:50:38.360 --> 01:50:42.240
And to just put in
context why it's so rare

01:50:42.240 --> 01:50:47.090
that this station actually
succeeded in the Northwest is

01:50:47.090 --> 01:50:53.970
because that area is extremely
rural, poor, very agricultural,

01:50:53.970 --> 01:50:56.590
very extremely conservative,

01:50:56.590 --> 01:51:00.960
all of the political positions
are held by the agricultural,

01:51:00.960 --> 01:51:03.940
representatives of the
agricultural industry.

01:51:03.940 --> 01:51:06.460
And so, there was a lot of fear

01:51:06.460 --> 01:51:09.940
about the station
coming into that area.

01:51:09.940 --> 01:51:12.790
And just, I don't
want to say a lot

01:51:12.790 --> 01:51:14.090
