02:16:15.570 --> 02:16:18.340
A little bit of background.

02:16:18.340 --> 02:16:22.770
Radio Haiti as a political
source in the voice of democracy

02:16:22.770 --> 02:16:28.650
in Haiti began in 1971, when
Jean Dominique, the station,

02:16:28.650 --> 02:16:31.640
the station's owner
bought the station.

02:16:31.640 --> 02:16:36.200
And over the next 30 years he
and his wife, Michele Montas,

02:16:36.200 --> 02:16:39.410
created this voice of democracy.

02:16:39.410 --> 02:16:43.230
And they kept going, even when
the station was off the air

02:16:43.230 --> 02:16:45.630
and they were in exile
in New York City.

02:16:45.630 --> 02:16:48.420
They came back twice to Haiti
before Jean Dominique was

02:16:48.420 --> 02:16:50.830
assassinated in 2000.

02:16:50.830 --> 02:16:55.160
If you're interested in that
story and it's an amazing story,

02:16:55.160 --> 02:16:58.110
Jonathan Demme made
a movie about him.

02:16:58.110 --> 02:16:59.410
It's a documentary.

02:16:59.410 --> 02:17:01.370
It's called the Agronomist.

02:17:01.370 --> 02:17:04.630
In 2013 10 years after
the station closed,

02:17:04.630 --> 02:17:07.150
because Michele kept the station
open for another three years

02:17:07.150 --> 02:17:09.420
after the assassination.

02:17:09.420 --> 02:17:12.160
