interest is really driven

02:58:49.060 --> 02:58:56.910
by a desire to tell a
narrative about democracy,

02:58:56.910 --> 02:58:58.210
both in the United
States and Haiti.

02:58:58.210 --> 02:58:59.510
It's about Creole.

02:58:59.510 --> 02:59:00.810
It's about the diaspora.

02:59:00.810 --> 02:59:02.110
It's about living in exile.

02:59:02.110 --> 02:59:07.140
But, one thing that I
find incredibly unique

02:59:07.140 --> 02:59:11.070
about [foreign language] is
really kind of the desire

02:59:11.070 --> 02:59:12.500
to decolonize a university
space.

02:59:12.500 --> 02:59:17.820
What does it mean to be
a political radio show

02:59:17.820 --> 02:59:22.070
within a university
setting, particularly

02:59:22.070 --> 02:59:26.630
like Columbia University?

02:59:26.630 --> 02:59:32.350
